{{Quote|Uh, listen, is it true what they say&hellip;I mean when they send seniors like me out on their first command assignments to see if we can handle it. Are most of these missions walkovers?''"<br />"''Ain't no walkovers where the Rebels are concerned, Cadet Leader, I don't care what they say on the holonews.|[[Cadet Leader]] [[Kyle Katarn]] and [[Sergeant major/Legends|Sergeant Major]] [[Hong]]|audio=OmegaExcercise-DFSftE.flac|<ref name="Dark Forces: Soldier for the Empire audio drama">[[Dark Forces: Soldier for the Empire (audio drama)|''Dark Forces: Soldier for the Empire'' audio drama]]</ref>}}
An '''Omega Exercise''' was a training tactic used by the [[Imperial Academy/Legends|Imperial Academy]]. In such an exercise, a [[Cadet/Legends|cadet]] would be placed in command of a [[Platoon/Legends|platoon]] of [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtroopers]] as a [[Cadet Leader|cadet leader]] and sent into actual combat to ascertain the cadet's resolve under fire. The senior officer's report and opinion was important for the final score. A satisfactory score was required to graduate the Academy; those who failed to gain such a score in their Omega Exercise would be flushed out of the Academy and sent to serve as an enlisted soldier.

[[Kyle Katarn]]'s Omega Exercise was the [[1 BBY/Legends|1 BBY]] [[Battle of AX-456|raid on AX-456]].

